cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (MM) techniques for synthesizing visible face images from thermal imagery. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of regularization terms to improve the quality of synthesized images, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.MM). The paper also reports on the results of facial landmark detection, which is a critical part of the face recognition process and is often studied in the context of machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the potential benefits of synthesized visible face imagery for human analysts, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
